<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="h-full">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Protocol - Inslash</title>
    <link href="/css/styles.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link
        href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;0,900;1,400;1,700;1,900&display=swap"
        rel="stylesheet">
</head>

<body class="font-sans antialiased bg-[#020617] text-slate-300 min-h-screen flex flex-col bg-grid">

    <%- include('partials/auth-navbar') %>

        <!-- Content -->
        <main class="flex-grow max-w-[1000px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 lg:px-16 py-32 relative z-10 w-full">
            <header class="mb-24 gsap-reveal">
                <div class="text-[10px] font-black text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-[0.4em] mb-4">Security Document
                    01-P</div>
                <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-black text-white mb-6 tracking-tighter leading-[0.9]">
                    Privacy <br />
                    <span class="text-indigo-500">Protocol.</span>
                </h1>
                <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest italic">Effective Specification:
                    February 20, 2026</p>
            </header>

            <article class="space-y-24 gsap-reveal">
                <section class="border-l-2 border-indigo-500/20 pl-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white mb-6 uppercase tracking-widest text-[14px]">1. Information
                        Ingestion</h2>
                    <div
                        class="prose prose-invert prose-slate max-w-none font-medium leading-relaxed text-slate-400 space-y-6">
                        <p>We collect system-minimum metadata required for protocol stability. This includes
                            cryptographic identities and operational logs telemetry.</p>
                        <ul class="space-y-3 list-none p-0">
                            <li class="flex items-center gap-3"><span
                                    class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-indigo-500 rounded-full"></span> Account Credentials (SHA-512
                                Encrypted)</li>
                            <li class="flex items-center gap-3"><span
                                    class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-indigo-500 rounded-full"></span> API Authentication Tokens
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-center gap-3"><span
                                    class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-indigo-500 rounded-full"></span> Transport Layer Telemetry
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class="border-l-2 border-indigo-500/20 pl-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white mb-6 uppercase tracking-widest text-[14px]">2.
                        Cryptographic Security</h2>
                    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-slate max-w-none font-medium leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
                        <p>Inslash utilizes enterprise-grade Argon2id and SHA-512 hashing vectors. Every fragment of
                            sensitive data is isolated within an immutable Passport string, featuring unique per-user
                            salts and optional hardware-security peppering.</p>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class="border-l-2 border-indigo-500/20 pl-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white mb-6 uppercase tracking-widest text-[14px]">3. Data
                        Sovereignty</h2>
                    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-slate max-w-none font-medium leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
                        <p>Your data is strictly confined to the Inslash ecosystem. We enforce a zero-sharing policy
                            with third-party analytical or advertising networks. Decryption is mathematically impossible
                            by design.</p>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class="border-l-2 border-indigo-500/20 pl-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white mb-6 uppercase tracking-widest text-[14px]">4. Operational
                        Persistence</h2>
                    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-slate max-w-none font-medium leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
                        <p>Metadata remains cached as long as the account remains active in the registry. Terminal
                            account deletion triggers a total cryptographic purge of all associated identities within 72
                            hours.</p>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class="border-l-2 border-indigo-500/20 pl-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white mb-6 uppercase tracking-widest text-[14px]">5. Protocol
                        Adjustments</h2>
                    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-slate max-w-none font-medium leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
                        <p>We reserve the right to upgrade this protocol as security standards evolve. Significant
                            shifts in cryptography will be broadcast via system-wide notifications.</p>
                    </div>
                </section>
            </article>

            <section class="mt-32 pt-24 border-t border-white/5 gsap-reveal">
                <h3 class="text-sm font-black text-white uppercase tracking-widest mb-6 italic">Protocol Contact</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-500 font-medium">For inquiries regarding the privacy specification, reach out via
                    the secure channel: <a href="mailto:protocol@inslash.security"
                        class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300 underline underline-offset-4">protocol@inslash.security</a>
                </p>
            </section>
        </main>

        <%- include('partials/auth-footer') %>

            <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/3.12.2/gsap.min.js"></script>
            <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/3.12.2/ScrollTrigger.min.js"></script>
            <script>
                gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);
                document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
                    gsap.utils.toArray(".gsap-reveal").forEach((el) => {
                        gsap.from(el, {
                            scrollTrigger: {
                                trigger: el,
                                start: "top 90%",
                            },
                            y: 30,
                            opacity: 0,
                            duration: 1,
                            ease: "power4.out"
                        });
                    });
                });
            </script>
</body>

</html>